-- Bush: Confident of economy's long-term health
-- 
-- Wed Mar 12, 2008 12:37pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/12/us-usa-economy-bush-idUSWAT00911120080312

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - President George W. Bush said on Wednesday the U.S. economy was in a difficult period but that he was confident of its long-term health. 

 "We've entered another period of difficult times," Bush said in a speech to the U.S. Hispanic Chamber of Commerce. "I'm confident in the long term for the United States economy. I know we're resilient ... I know we'll withstand these times." (Reporting by  Matt Spetalnick , Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)